Pick n Pay Surges Most in 14 Months on Franklins’ Australia Sale Approval

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-08-25T07:37:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/pick-n-pay-surges-most-in-14-months-on-franklins-australia-sale-approval.html
Pick n Pay Stores Ltd. (PIK) ,  South
Africa ’s second-biggest food retailer, surged the most in almost
14 months after an Australian court granted Metcash Ltd.
approval to buy the Franklins chain from Pick n Pay.  The stock rallied as much as 3.8 percent, the most since
July 2010, to 39.14 rand and traded 2.1 percent up at 38.50 rand
by 9:37 a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
